parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to serious injury or death in the event of a crash, as the airbags may not deploy or may deploy improperly.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is illuminated

the passenger airbag is turned off

the driver seat broke and twisted
and the headrest dislodged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear wheel speed sensor can cause the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) to malfunction, leading to unpredictable braking performance, increased stopping distances, and potentially accidents.
symptoms: ABS and brake lights illuminate on the dashboard
intermittent or permanent loss of ABS functionality
vibrations or shuddering of the brake pedal
and reduced braking power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of the speed sensor connectors can cause the ABS system to malfunction, leading to unpredictable braking performance, increased stopping distances, and potentially accidents.
symptoms: ABS and brake lights illuminate on the dashboard
intermittent or permanent loss of ABS functionality
vibrations or shuddering of the brake pedal
and reduced braking power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the brake system can cause loss of braking power, increased stopping distances, and potentially accidents.
symptoms: Spongy or soft brake pedal
delayed or incomplete braking response
vibrations or shuddering of the brake pedal
and reduced braking power.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Axle Beam Failure due to Corrosion
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear axle beam can cause the wheel to break off, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The rear wheel is leaning inward
the vehicle is not tracking properly
a strange sound is coming from the rear area
and the axle beam is cracked or broken at the weld.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Lower Control Arm Bolt Failure due to Corrosion
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front lower control arm bolt can cause the control arm to separate from the subframe, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: A clunking noise is heard during vehicle operation
the vehicle hesitates
and a loud noise is coming from the front end. The bolt head and portion of the shank are missing due to corrosion and fatigue failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission problems can cause the vehicle to hesitate, vibrate, and pull to one side, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle has to be warmed up before gears can be changed properly
the transmission gears do not engage at all
and the vehicle pulls to the right or left while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear wheel hub bearing can cause the wheel to break off, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The rear wheel hub bearings are failing
and the parts are only available at the dealer at a very expensive price.
